Health Minister Zweli Mkhize revealed that there are now 38 coronavirus cases in South Africa. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Health Minister Zweli Mkhize says that the number of new coronavirus cases in South Africa is a matter of concern. Mkhize was speaking after the number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in the country rose by 14. There are now 38 coronavirus cases in South Africa. READ: What is a virus? How do they spread and how do they make us sick? President Cyril Ramaphosa has called an urgent cabinet meeting on Sunday to discuss the outbreak. The minister says he is concerned about the rising number of cases. "The rapid rise in the numbers is a matter of concern that requires cabinet to sit down and look at it," Mkhize said. "So the president has called for a report to be tabled which indicates the trends and challenges that we can see and therefore come with proposals." - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp.